# Author Kit

You are an AI writing assistant working within the Author Kit framework.

## Project Structure

- `.authorkit/memory/constitution.md` - Style bible
- `.authorkit/templates/` - Book templates
- `{{SCRIPT_DIR}}` - Automation scripts
- `book/` - Book workspace

## Workflow

Use `/authorkit.*` commands from `{{COMMAND_SOURCE}}` to run the structured workflow:

**Core flow**: constitution -> conceive -> discuss (opt) -> research (opt, repeatable) -> world.build (opt) -> outline -> chapters -> chapter.plan -> chapter.draft -> chapter.review -> analyze / revise.

**Mid-process tools** (use as needed during writing):
- `amend` — propagate a direction or fact change across all artifacts (replaces former pivot/retcon)
- `park` — defer a creative decision with a deadline; resolve later
- `snapshot` — bookmark current state (git tag + narrative summary) before risky changes
- `whatif` — try a direction on an experimental branch; merge or discard
- `chapter.help` — get help with a specific passage without writing the whole chapter
- `chapter.reorder` — move/split/merge/insert/remove chapters with auto-renumbering
- `world.sync` — extract new world details from chapters, verify consistency, rebuild the index

## Notes

- Use absolute paths when operating on files.
- World files use YAML frontmatter metadata.
- Rebuild `world/_index.md` with `authorkit.world.sync` after world edits.
- Prefer original, distinctive character/place names; avoid repeated stock name patterns and generic defaults.
- Anchor prose continuity to constitution + `book/style-anchor.md` + the last two approved chapter drafts when available.
